This paper is about sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a cross-lingual approach to sentiment analysis that incorporates sentiment information into bilingual distributional representations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Cybernetics (cs.CY).
